Hungary’s Outlook Cut to Negative at Fitch on Budget Loosening
description: Fitch Ratings cut the outlook on Hungary’s credit score to negative from stable, after a loosening of budget targets to accommodate Prime Minister Viktor Orban’s pre-election spending.

title: ‘There is no Mamdani effect’: Manhattan luxury home sales surge after mayoral election, undercutting predictions of doom and escape to Florida
description: Signed contracts for Manhattan homes over $4 million skyrocketed 25%; “the idea that people would flee New York was overblown,” said realtor Donna Olshan.

title: FIA election to go ahead despite legal challenge
description: The FIA's presidential election is set to go ahead next week, although legal proceedings could overturn the result in February.

title: Republican wins US House election in Tennessee, bolstering party majority
Trump-backed Republican Matt Van Epps wins US House special election in Tennessee
description: Republican Matt Van Epps won a nationally watched special election in Tennessee for a seat in the U.S. House on Tuesday, maintaining his party’s grip on the district with help from President Donald Trump.  A military veteran and former state general services commissioner from Nashville, Van Epps defeated Democratic state Rep. Aftyn Behn to represent the 7th Congressional District.

title: 2 conservative operatives get probation for robocalls to discourage Black Detroit voters in 2020
description: Two conservative political operatives were sentenced to probation Monday for a scheme to discourage Black Detroit voters from voting by mail in the 2020 presidential election, the last court hearing in a multistate effort to blast thousands of robocalls.  Jacob Wohl and Jack Burkman were accused of creating robocalls that warned people they could be hounded by police, debt collectors and government vaccine bureaucrats if they voted by mail.  In August, Wohl and Burkman pleaded no contest to voter intimidation, conspiracy and computer crimes after a long, unsuccessful effort to challenge the charges on free speech grounds.

title: The S&P 500 could hit 7,000 this week, while Trump hints at a Fed chair pick and Washington eyes this special election
description: "The S&P 500 would need to rise by just 2.2% to reach 7,000. That could happen this coming week, in our view."

title: Trump to Pardon Ex-Honduras Leader Convicted of Drug Trafficking
description: President Donald Trump said he plans to pardon a former president of Honduras who’s serving a decades-long US sentence for cocaine trafficking, two days before the nation’s election.

title: Trump seizes control of Republicans' 2026 election strategy with his presidency on the line
description: By Nandita Bose and Tim Reid WASHINGTON (Reuters) -President Donald Trump isn't on the ballot in next November's midterm elections, but he’s plunging into them with his own presidency at stake.

title: The analyst who once predicted the ‘end of capitalism’ sees Zohran Mamdani’s election as a ‘day of reckoning coming in’—and corporates only have themselves to blame
description: Albert Edwards says Zohran Mamdani’s policies are “lunacy,” but big companies “laid the seeds for their own destruction.”
